

	 
      And then moonlight slides unto the ceiling it wakes her, and she lies in the hammock, her mind skating.    She finds reset as opposed to sleep the truly pleasurable state.  If she were a writer she would collect her pencils and notebooks and favorite cat and write in bed.  Strangers and lovers would never get passed the locked door.  To rest was to receive all aspects of the world without judgement.  A bath in the sea, a fuck with the soldier who never knew your name.  Tenderness towards the unknown and anonymous, which is a tenderness to the self.   - The English Patient -  
     
    
